modules.description: This module provides functions for opening and closing binary input/output channels with LZ4 compression handled in the background via named pipes and separate processes. It works with standard input and output channels (`in_channel` and `out_channel`) and supports reading from and writing to compressed files without exposing compression logic to the user. Concrete use cases include efficiently reading from or writing to LZ4-compressed binary files, such as log files or large data dumps, while maintaining a simple I/O interface.
